https://leetcode.com/problems/valid-elements-in-an-array/description/

QUESTION:
Input: nums = [1,2,4,2,3,2]
Output: [1,2,4,3,2]
It is strictly greater than every element to its left.
It is strictly greater than every element to its right.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SOLUTION:
Checking precalculated values.
->Maximum element on the left for every index
->Maximum element on the right for every index
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME  COMPLEXITY:O(n)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(n)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
leftgreat[i] → max element in index range 0 to i-1
rightgreat[i] → max element in index range i+1 to n-1
Construct two arrays:
Loop left → construct leftgreat
Loop right → construct rightgreat (in one loop by using j=n-i-1)
Loop through elements:
If element satisfies either of the following conditions, add element:
Element lies on boundary (i == 0 || i == n-1)
OR
Element is greater than all elements to its left
OR
Element is greater than all elements to its right
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> findValidElements(int[] nums) {
        int n=nums.length;
        List<Integer>ar=new ArrayList<>();
        int leftgreat[]=new int[n];
        int rightgreat[]=new int[n];
        int lmax=nums[0];
        int rmax=nums[0];
        if(n==1){
            ar.add(nums[0]);
            return ar;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(i==0){
                leftgreat[i]=0;
            }else{
                leftgreat[i]=Math.max(nums[i-1],leftgreat[i-1]);
            }
        }
        for(int i=n-1;i>=0;i--){
            if(i==n-1){
                rightgreat[i]=0;
            }else{
                rightgreat[i]=Math.max(nums[i+1],rightgreat[i+1]);
            }
        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(nums[i]>leftgreat[i]||nums[i]>rightgreat[i]||i==0||i==n-1){
                ar.add(nums[i]);
            }
        }
        return ar;
    }
}
